We are trying to increase the usability and visibility of our docs and samples.
the main idea is to make them easy to discover and increase the usage of cli commands in the process.
@SyntaxC4 as he provided these fwlinks

Another awesome thing is that newer Pythons also have set comprehensions, like

        out = {addr.get_port() for vhost in matching_vhosts for addr in vhost.addrs}

Sadly, that's incompatible with Python 2.6 so I don't think we would be allowed to use it. :frowning:

I guess this would be computationally a bit more expensive, but might tidy up the line?

```
                var tvc = ' .th-view-content';
                var classes = '.selected-job,' +
                    tvc + ' .job-btn.btn-red,' +
                    tvc + ' .job-btn.btn-orange,' +
                    tvc + ' .job-btn.btn-purple';
                $rootScope.$emit(thEvents.changeSelection, 'next', classes);
```

This handles the case of an initial render, you'll still want to do a `setProps` after this first expect.

```
const toolbar = mount(
      <Toolbar type={'code'} />
    );
expect(toolbar.text()).to.contain('Convert to Markdown Cell');
toolbar.setProps({ type: 'markdown' })
expect(toolbar.text()).to.contain('Convert to Code Cell');
```

